<TITLE> N'ganj train-truck collision kills one, snaps links </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 29 (bdnews24.com) Rail communication between Dhaka-Narayanganj remained suspended after a train smashed into a truck on Shyampur level-crossing Tuesday morning killing one person. Kadamtali police said the Dhaka bound train hit the truck at around 7am. Sixty-year old Abdus Sattar, a vendor, died on the spot when he was hit by fragments of the damaged truck. Four others, injured in the accident, were admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital in a critical condition. bdnews2
